1/ root files:
package - view dependencies
you can see the version of react your using
scripts - how npm start works

3/ public
index.html
root folder that gets served by webserver.
has an html page - you will never add files here
script files get injected here.

<div id="root"><div> = where react app is mounted

4/ Src - script files
Your react app is here!!
index.js = you can see how the 'root' is hooked.
it says "add the app component to the root"
app.js - a component.  when you create the app - it's the only
component it uses.


2/ node_modules
holds dependency code
